The paper discusses the design space of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their applications in machine learning problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs in various applications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the methodology for exploring the design space of CNNs, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
